\displaystyle\sum_{k=0}^{n} \binom{R}{k}\binom{M}{(n-k)}=\displaystyle \binom{R+M}{n}
\sum_{k=0}^n \binom{R}k\binom{M}{n-k}=\sum_{k=0}^n \binom{R}k\binom{(R+M)-R}{n-k}=\binom{R+M}n
